msgSnippet: Start at http://www.junit.org.  You can find the software, and lots of information on how to use it.  It really is very simple to write.  The hard part is
messageBody:
Start at http://www.junit.org You can find the software, and lots of
information on how to use it. It really is very simple to write. The hard
part is figuring out what tests you need to write.

For that, there are several good books. Look at
http://www.junit.org/news/book/index.htm. I like Test-Driven Development, A
Practical Guide, by David Astels. Kent Beck's Test-Driven Development By
Example is also excellent.

Good luck.


--
Jim McMaster
